title: Live at Fraternity Village
text:
Live at Fraternity Village Oct 08, 2015 
Searsmont — Rose & The Wayfaring Strangers will perform Saturday, Oct. 17, from 6 to 8 p.m. at Fraternity Village Store, from 6 to 8 p.m. The store is located downtown at 12 Main St./Route 131. 
The band’s style of music ranges from Hank Williams, Patsy Cline, Alan Jackson to Merle Haggard, with a little older rock and some bluegrass gospel thrown in. Rose & The Wayfaring Strangers have performed up and down the Midcoast area and always enjoy seeing people sing along and smile during their performances. 
The store offers sandwiches, pizza, pies and more to fuel the toe tapping and singing along. For more information on Rose & The Wayfaring Strangers performances or bookings, contact Rosey Gerry at 975-5432 or roskari@gmail.com. 
Courier Publications’ A&E Editor Dagney C. Ernest can be reached at (207) 594-4401, ext. 115; or dernest@courierpublicationsllc.com.
